<br>
Personally when I host a raid, I expect people to put a little bit of effort into it, and read what I say in the raid description, if I say you should know how to get there etc, then that is a requirement of the raid.  Anyone can buy an invis potion if they don't know anyone who can cast invis.<br>
<br>
Everyone does things different, and if someone wants to show people the way beforehand etc, more power to them.<br>
<br>
Anyone who knows me knows that I am a stickler for being on time etc, I personally value my time quite a bit, and because my play time is limited, I prefer to do things in the most time efficient manner possible when I am able to play.<br>
<br>
I agree that level does not equal knowledge, a level 49 may know more about the game and be a better player then a 55 who doesn't have a clue.  I didn't say one or the other was important, I think both are important.  I do not doubt that a level 49 could surive in UP, I'm sure they could do quite fine.  The idea I was suggesting was something that 1 or 2 groups of 55+ could do for a couple hours on a weeknight .  Not something that required rounding up hoards of level 49s and showing them the way etc all day until we are ready.<br>
