I see a lot of raid leaders taking the stance of &quot;you don't like my raids? don't sign up!&quot;  I'm not fond of this attitude but they have every right to have that attitude and can set the any rules they choose for the Federation.  You must realize something though, by making a raid 55+ you turn away a lot of capable people from the Federation who may want to go on the raid.  You also alienate the people who do not agree with your strict rules.  <br>
(# of people wanting to go on a raid) - (too low of level) - (those choosing the &quot;don't sign up!&quot; offer you made) = Total number of people available to go on a raid.<br>
If the result is enough for you to lead the raid and it be a success to you, more power to you.  If you consistantly don't have enough people to do what you want to accomplish on the raid, perhaps you should re-evaluate your level limit, rules or both?<br>
In the end: The game is what you make of it, can we really ask for any more than to have a little fun?  Rock on. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
